    "body": "This does seem to capture the tune-ability of genesis that is desired, but ups the complexity even from the previous calculation.\r\n\r\n@protolambda we do have genesis state initialization tests, but just don't have much coverage. Regardless of what we do here, we should increase the coverage to avoid more issues in genesis time calculations. With sufficient consensus tests here, I wouldn't expect this increase in complexity to be an issue. \r\n\r\nOr is the issue amplified by the eth1 tracking?",
